<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,684,1539]" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">
This is the most widespread species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1862" box="[576,702,684,710]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[576,702,684,710]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">Megalestes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, occurring throughout South 
<collectingCountry box="[1025,1092,684,710]" name="China" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1105,1181,684,710]" country="China" name="Fujian" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">Fujian</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1190,1324,684,710]" country="China" name="Guangdong" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">Guangdong</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1333,1432,684,710]" country="China" name="Guangxi" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">Guangxi</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[151,250,720,746]" country="China" name="Guizhou" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">Guizhou</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[263,339,721,747]" country="China" name="Henan" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">Henan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[352,429,721,747]" country="China" name="Hunan" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">Hunan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[443,527,720,746]" country="China" name="Jiangxi" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">Jiangxi</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[539,632,720,746]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[644,733,721,747]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion box="[795,897,720,747]" country="China" name="Zhejiang" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">Zhejiang</collectingRegion>
) extending to 
<collectingCountry box="[1062,1160,720,746]" name="Vietnam" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1172,1256,720,746]" name="Bhutan" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">Bhutan</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[1318,1379,720,746]" name="India" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">India</collectingCountry>
. It is also the only species distributed on both sides of the Himalayas. The diagnostic character for this mid-sized species is the base of the basal tooth on the paraproct bulged, covered in dense setae (
<figureCitation box="[1072,1139,792,819]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1319,1343]" captionTargetBox="[168,1412,187,1286]" captionTargetId="figure-17@19.[163,1423,181,1295]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 6. Line drawing of male paraprocts (lateral view). a) australis; b) distans; c) gyalsey; d) kurahashii; e) major; f) haui; g) heros; h) omeiensis; i) micans; j) micans; k) riccii; l) irma." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4407497" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4407497/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
i-j). This species is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1935" box="[263,359,829,854]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="riccii">
<emphasis box="[263,359,829,854]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">M. riccii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and this was confirmed by molecular analysis (
<figureCitation box="[901,969,828,855]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1978,2002]" captionTargetBox="[213,1367,496,1949]" captionTargetId="figure-214@20.[211,1375,489,1954]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 7. Phylogenetic reconstruction from ITS data modified based on BI and ML trees, with both posterior probabilities (right) and bootstrap values (left) shown." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4407499" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4407499/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
