<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,684,1539]" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">
In the description of 
<taxonomicName authority=", Chao (1947)" authorityName=", Chao" authorityYear="1947" box="[433,699,864,891]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chengi">
<emphasis box="[433,545,864,890]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">M. chengi</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Chao, H. - F." box="[559,699,864,890]" pageId="17" pageNumber="262" pagination="15 - 25" refId="ref13540" refString="Chao, H. - F. (1947) On the systematic position, nymphal charaters and new species of the genera Megalestes and Sinolestes (Odonata). Biological Bulletin, Fukien Christian University, 6, 15 - 25." type="journal article" year="1947">Chao (1947)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
only compared his material with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Needham" authorityYear="1930" box="[1076,1174,864,890]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heros">
<emphasis box="[1076,1174,864,890]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">M. heros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a totally different species. Later, 
<bibRefCitation author="Chao, H. - F." box="[282,424,900,927]" pageId="17" pageNumber="262" pagination="187 - 196" refId="ref13620" refString="Chao, H. - F. (1965) A study of the Chinese dragonflies of the genus Megalestes Selys, with description of a new species (Odonata: Synlestidae). Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 2, 187 - 196." type="journal article" year="1965">Chao (1965)</bibRefCitation>
stated that the differences between 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Chao" authorityYear="1947" box="[829,943,900,926]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chengi">
<emphasis box="[829,943,900,926]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">M. chengi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Needham" authorityYear="1930" box="[998,1115,901,926]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="micans">
<emphasis box="[998,1115,901,926]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">M. micans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
included the middle portion of the middle lobe of the pronotum green, not yellow (feature 2), and the base of the basal tooth of the paraproct slightly, but not greatly, bulged (feature 15). However, all these characters occur in intraspecies variation (Discussion section). Although both 
<bibRefCitation author="Chao, H. - F." box="[474,614,1008,1035]" pageId="17" pageNumber="262" pagination="187 - 196" refId="ref13620" refString="Chao, H. - F. (1965) A study of the Chinese dragonflies of the genus Megalestes Selys, with description of a new species (Odonata: Synlestidae). Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 2, 187 - 196." type="journal article" year="1965">Chao (1965)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Asahina, S." box="[666,853,1008,1035]" pageId="17" pageNumber="262" pagination="1 - 18" refId="ref13502" refString="Asahina, S. (1985 b) Contributions to the taxonomic knowledge of the Megalestes species of continental South Asia (Odonata, Synlestidae). Cho-Cho, 8 (10), 1 - 18." type="journal article" year="1985">Asahina (1985b)</bibRefCitation>
have emphasized that 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Chao" authorityYear="1947" box="[1106,1218,1008,1034]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chengi">
<emphasis box="[1106,1218,1008,1034]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">M. chengi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was very similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Needham" authorityYear="1930" box="[151,267,1045,1070]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="micans">
<emphasis box="[151,267,1045,1070]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">M. micans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, neither author confirmed that they are really the same species. We examined eight of the type specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Chao" authorityYear="1947" box="[182,295,1080,1106]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chengi">
<emphasis box="[182,295,1080,1106]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">M. chengi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
deposited in 
<collectionCode box="[447,509,1080,1106]" country="0" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/043p-ts4f" name="Institut Zoologii Akademii Nauk Ukraini - Institute of Zoology of the Academy of Sciences of Ukraine" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">IZAS</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode box="[564,626,1080,1106]" country="China" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/3v6b-6ji1" name="Institute of Entomology" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">IEAS</collectionCode>
including the 
<typeStatus box="[789,887,1080,1106]" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">holotype</typeStatus>
and found no evident morphological differences with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Needham" authorityYear="1930" box="[211,330,1117,1142]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="micans">
<emphasis box="[211,330,1117,1142]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">M. micans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The molecular analyses also suggested that these two are the same species (
<figureCitation box="[1224,1295,1116,1143]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1978,2002]" captionTargetBox="[213,1367,496,1949]" captionTargetId="figure-214@20.[211,1375,489,1954]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 7. Phylogenetic reconstruction from ITS data modified based on BI and ML trees, with both posterior probabilities (right) and bootstrap values (left) shown." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4407499" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4407499/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Therefore, based on both morphological and molecular evidence (
<figureCitation box="[775,844,1152,1178]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1567,1591]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1535]" captionTargetId="figure-17@21.[151,1436,181,1543]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 8. Molecular and morphology-based species delimitation of Megalestes. M: morphological character method; lg: genital ligula; app: caudal appendages, including cerci and paraprocts; GD: genetic distance; TC: traditional classification." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4407501" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4407501/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
), we confirm that 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Chao" authorityYear="1947" box="[1057,1170,1152,1178]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chengi">
<emphasis box="[1057,1170,1152,1178]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">M. chengi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Needham" authorityYear="1930" box="[151,268,1189,1214]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="micans">
<emphasis box="[151,268,1189,1214]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">M. micans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,684,1539]" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">
As we have previously discussed, diagnostic characters of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wilson" authorityYear="2004" box="[867,975,1224,1250]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="discus">
<emphasis box="[867,975,1224,1250]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">M. discus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cannot separate it from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Needham" authorityYear="1930" box="[1253,1371,1225,1250]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="micans">
<emphasis box="[1253,1371,1225,1250]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">M. micans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Wilson, K. D. P. &amp; Xu, Z. F." pageId="17" pageNumber="262" pagination="87 - 128" refId="ref15285" refString="Wilson, K. D. P. &amp; Xu, Z. F. (2007) Odonata of Guangdong, Hong Kong and Macau, South China, part 1: Zygoptera. International Journal of Odonatology, 10, 87 - 128. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 13887890.2007.9748292" type="journal article" year="2007">Wilson &amp; Xu (2007)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wilson" authorityYear="2004" box="[524,631,1260,1286]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="discus">
<emphasis box="[524,631,1260,1286]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">M. discus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have “inferior appendages without a basal pair of stout spines or robust teeth,” which is incorrect, and “occipital margin with/without transverse yellow spot” (feature 1) supports our opinion that this character is not stable. We examined the diagnostic character photos of the 
<typeStatus box="[1148,1244,1333,1359]" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">paratype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wilson" authorityYear="2004" box="[1284,1354,1332,1358]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="discus">
<emphasis box="[1284,1354,1332,1358]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">discus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<quantity box="[1373,1416,1332,1359]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="262" unit="m" value="1.0">1 m</quantity>
#, Mangshan (near Babaoshan), Shikengkong, S 
<collectingRegion box="[674,751,1369,1395]" country="China" name="Hunan" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">Hunan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[763,833,1368,1394]" name="China" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<date box="[845,980,1368,1394]" pageId="17" pageNumber="262" value="2000-06-26">26-VI-2000</date>
, K.D.P. Wilson leg.), which were kindly sent by K. D. P. Wilson, and found that all the characters are consistent with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Needham" authorityYear="1930" box="[1013,1129,1405,1430]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="micans">
<emphasis box="[1013,1129,1405,1430]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">M. micans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. No further information on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lahiri" authorityYear="1987" box="[151,349,1440,1466]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="raychoudhurii">
<emphasis box="[151,349,1440,1466]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">M. raychoudhurii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been published after its original description. According to the features of caudal appendages and genital ligula in the original description and figures, there is no difference between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lahiri" authorityYear="1987" box="[1150,1349,1476,1502]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="raychoudhurii">
<emphasis box="[1150,1349,1476,1502]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">M. raychoudhurii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Needham" authorityYear="1930" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="micans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">M. micans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We believe that both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wilson" authorityYear="2004" box="[481,551,1512,1538]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="discus">
<emphasis box="[481,551,1512,1538]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">discus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lahiri" authorityYear="1987" box="[606,803,1512,1538]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="raychoudhurii">
<emphasis box="[606,803,1512,1538]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">M. raychoudhurii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are junior synonyms of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Needham" authorityYear="1930" box="[1076,1192,1513,1538]" class="Insecta" family="Synlestidae" genus="Megalestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="17" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="micans">
<emphasis box="[1076,1192,1513,1538]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="262">M. micans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
